title: Experts warn of child care industry turmoil ahead
description: An end to federal pandemic funding this year could send prices for child care up, forcing businesses to close, and people — especially moms — out of the workforce.
author: Sarah Ewall-Wice

title: Michigan Republicans are in turmoil as their leaders navigate tricky Trump terrain
description: After a shellacking that wiped them out of power in state government for the first time in 40 years, Michigan Republicans are wrestling with an uncertain future.
author: Henry J. Gomez

title: The blue Midwest is where DeSantis’s school crackdowns ‘go to die’
description: Illinois Gov. J.B. Pritzker and other Democrats are treating red-state culture-warring as a foil.
author: Greg Sargent

title: Trump’s early-state poll problem
description: The polls nationally have narrowed. But the polls in the states that matter more in the GOP primaries are actually worse for him.
author: Aaron Blake

title: Some Democrats are worried about Harris’s political prospects
description: In interviews, more than a dozen Democratic leaders and activists expressed misgivings about Kamala Harris at the top of the Democratic Party.
author: Cleve R. Wootson Jr.

title: Red, white and (increasingly) blue. How Democrats look to take advantage of state 'trifectas'
description: With a plurality of Americans living in Democratic "trifecta" states, here's how Dems hope to make impact on abortion access, LGBTQ rights and more.
author: USA TODAY, Phillip M. Bailey, USA TODAY
